            "subject": "LU-5867 lfsck: Enable --create_mdtobj flag"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-09-11 23:55:43.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-12-03 02:29:07.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-1452 scrub: OI scrub skips uninitialized groups",
        "message": "LU-1452 scrub: OI scrub skips uninitialized groups\n\nIf the ldiskfs group descriptor is marked as LDISKFS_BG_INODE_UNINIT,\nthen means that the inodes in such group have never been initialized,\nso the otable based iterator can skip this group directly to speed up\nthe scanning.\n\nIf the iteration position reaches the unused inodes area in the\ngroup descriptor (indicated by bg_itable_unused), then skip the\nrest inodes in this group to reduce the scanning time.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ie8a2eb1269d288865ce51d40e211e3db54d062af\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/12737\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Lai Siyao <lai.siyao@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
